” to WooCommerce, allowing users to categorize their products into desired brands. Each brand can be named, described, and assigned an image. The brands can then be filtered, displaying all their products. Create a new brand A [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Bernat Torras";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3829:"<h2>WooCommerce Brands</h2>\n<p><a href="http://www.woothemes.com/products/brands/">http://www.woothemes.com/products/brands/</a></p>\n<h2>Fixed Issues</h2>\n<p>Synchronization of “Brands” thumbnails</p>\n<h2>Extension Description</h2>\n<p>This extension adds a new taxonomy named “Brands” to WooCommerce, allowing users to categorize their products into desired brands. Each brand can be named, described, and assigned an image. The brands can then be filtered, displaying all their products.</p>\n<h2>Create a new brand</h2>\n<p>A new submenu item appears under “Products” main section. From there, a user can create as many Brands as he/she likes.</p>\n<div id="attachment_435676" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/menu.png"><img class="wp-image-435676 size-medium" src="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/menu-300x287.png" alt="Creating a new Brand" width="300" height="287" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Creating a new Brand</p></div>\n<h2>Assigning a brand to a product</h2>\n<p>When editing a product, a user can check the desired brands in the new “Brands” metabox.</p>\n<div id="attachment_435677" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/product_brands.png"><img class="wp-image-435677 size-medium" src="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/product_brands-300x280.png" alt="Setting Brands for a product" width="300" height="280" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Setting Brands for a product</p></div>\n<h2>Translating Brands</h2>\n<p>Brands can be translated from the WCML GUI. A new “Brands” tab has been created to allow users to translate all their brands in the same manner that they translate product categories.</p>\n<div id="attachment_435678" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/wcml_brands.png"><img class="wp-image-435678 size-medium" src="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/wcml_brands-300x192.png" alt="Translating Brands" width="300" height="192" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating Brands</p></div>\n<h2>Synchronizing brands parents and thumbnail images</h2>\n<p>To enable the synchronization of brands parents and thumbnail images, the user should check the “Sync taxonomy (e.g. category) parents” option from WPML&gt;Translation Management&gt;Multilingual Content Setup.</p>\n<p>Once this option is enabled, the brands parents and thumbnail images will be automatically synchronized after each brand is translated.</p>\n<div id="attachment_435680" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/brands_TM.png"><img class="wp-image-435680 size-medium" src="http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/brands_TM-300x219.png" alt="Synchronizing brands" width="300" height="219" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Synchronizing brands</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=bAPdS4dgTOE:vgh_qPYZTC0:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=bAPdS4dgTOE:vgh_qPYZTC0:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http:/